<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Link Rot - URL Rotator</title>
    <link href="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@5.3.3/dist/css/bootstrap.min.css" rel="stylesheet" integrity="sha384-QWTKZyjpPEjISv5WaRU9OFeRpok6YctnYmDr5pNlyT2bRjXh0JMhjY6hW+ALEwIH" crossorigin="anonymous">
    <style>
        /* Background with blurry ambient light */
        body {
            background: linear-gradient(135deg, rgba(63, 94, 251, 0.8), rgba(252, 70, 107, 0.8));
            background-size: 200% 200%;
            animation: gradientAnimation 15s ease infinite;
            font-family: 'Arial', sans-serif;
            color: white;
        }

        /* Smooth gradient animation */
        @keyframes gradientAnimation {
            0% { background-position: 0% 50%; }
            50% { background-position: 100% 50%; }
            100% { background-position: 0% 50%; }
        }

        /* Content container styling */
        .container {
            backdrop-filter: blur(10px);
            background: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.5);
            padding: 2rem;
            border-radius: 15px;
            box-shadow: 0 10px 30px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.3);
        }

        /* Footer styling */
        footer {
            background: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.7);
        }

        a {
            text-decoration: none;
        }

        /* Fix table URL column size */
        table td a {
            display: block;
            max-width: 500px;
            white-space: normal; 
            word-wrap: break-word;
        }

        /* Medium screens (tablets) */
        @media (max-width: 992px) { /* Bootstrap "md" breakpoint */
            table td a {
                max-width: 150px; /* Slightly smaller for tablets */
            }
        }

        /* Small screens (phones) */
        @media (max-width: 576px) { /* Bootstrap "sm" breakpoint */
            table td a {
                max-width: 100px; /* Smallest size for phones */
            }
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <!-- Navbar -->
    <nav class="navbar navbar-expand-lg navbar-dark bg-dark">
        <div class="container-fluid">
            <a class="navbar-brand" href="/">Link Rot</a>
            <button class="navbar-toggler" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#navbarNav" aria-controls="navbarNav" aria-expanded="false" aria-label="Toggle navigation">
                <span class="navbar-toggler-icon"></span>
            </button>
            <div class="collapse navbar-collapse" id="navbarNav">
                <ul class="navbar-nav ms-auto">
                    <li class="nav-item">
                        <a class="nav-link " aria-current="page" href="/">Home</a>
                    </li>
                    <li class="nav-item">
                        <a class="nav-link active" href="about">About</a>
                    </li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </div>
    </nav>
    

    <!-- Main Content -->
    <div class="container mt-5">
        <h1 class="text-center mb-4">"Brain Rot" Your URLs</h1>
        <p class="text-center text-white">Quickly convert your URLs into "brainrot" URLs with ease!</p>

        <div id="thank-you" class="container mt-5 mb-5">
            <h2>How It Came To Be</h2>
            <p>
                I was looking at a link shortner, then wonder if there was away to make them human-readable. Thus, I came with the solution LinkRot because every combination of brainrot words make the same amount of sense. zero.
            </p>
        </div>

        <div id="thank-you" class="container mt-5 mb-5">
            <h2>Thank You</h2>
            <p>
                This project would not have been possible without the contributions and inspirations from the following sources:
            </p>
            <ul>
                <li>
                    <a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/GCSE/comments/1cho8sd/we_got_bored_in_biology_so_made_an_a_z_brain_rot/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
                        Reddit - Brainrot Alphabet Inspiration
                    </a>: Special thanks to the Redditors who created the original A-Z brainrot alphabet!
                </li>
                <li>
                    ChatGPT: A huge thank you to ChatGPT for turning a 3-day project into a half day project.
                <li>
                    <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=SLpUKAGnm-g" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
                        Web Dev Simplified - Responsive Navbar Tutorial
                    </a>: This amazing tutorial helped in building the basics for the project.
                </li>
            </ul>
        </div>
        

    </div>
    <footer class="text-white text-center py-3 mt-5">
        <small>@omeygunner on instagram</small>
    </footer>


    <script src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@5.3.3/dist/js/bootstrap.bundle.min.js" integrity="sha384-yNcp0+xKKMSTsrFI7UfdHQBsjDUbFVVBEspQm/ZBfQmkRmg9Xx0prOlx4WY1bD16" crossorigin="anonymous"></script>
</body>
</html>
